4 HJR___ COMMENDING MOLLY MEADOWS ON THE OCCASION OF HER
5 RETIREMENT.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with profound appreciation and highest
8 esteem that Molly Meadows is honored for her exceptional
9 dedication, commitment, and professionalism throughout her
10 tenure serving Houston County, Alabama, for nearly four
11 decades; and
12 WHEREAS, Molly Meadows was first appointed by Albert
13 McDonald, Secretary of Agriculture under the Governor Guy
14 Hunt Administration, in 1987; she served through 10 cycles
15 for presidential, gubernatorial, and local elections with
16 distinction as Chairman of the Board of Registrars in
17 Houston County, contributing significantly to maintaining
18 the integrity of the voter registration process and
19 encouragement of every person's right to vote; and
20 WHEREAS, she has exemplified the highest standards of
21 public service, good character, and servant leadership,
22 making the voter registration process available and
23 accessible for all residents of Houston County; and
24 WHEREAS, Molly was married for 58 years to Robert
25 Brook "Bo" Meadows before he passed in 2018; Mr. Meadows
26 worked in the business license division of the Houston
27 County Judge of Probate's Office; both Molly and Bo were
28 involved in civic and community service; Molly has a son,
Page 1

involved in civic and community service; Molly has a son,
HJR284 INTRODUCED
29 Brook Meadows; daughters, Misty Sheffield and Holly
30 Gagliano; 10 grandchildren; and seven great-grandchildren;
31 and
32 WHEREAS, it is the desire of the Legislature to
33 recognize and honor Molly Meadows for her invaluable
34 contributions, undeniable passion for her work, and loyal
35 service to Houston County and the State of Alabama upon the
36 occasion of her retirement effective March 31, 2026; now
37 therefore,
38 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
39 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Molly Meadows is hereby
40 commended on the occasion of her retirement as Chairman of
41 the Board of Registrars in Houston County, and this
42 resolution is offered to her in highest tribute and with
43 deepest appreciation along with best wishes as she embarks
44 upon her well-deserved retirement.
